 Ibrahim Shuaibu in Dutse Jigawa State Governor, Muhammad Badaru Abubakar, yesterday declared interest to contest the 2023 presidential election on the All Progressives Congress (APC) platform. The Special Adviser to the governor on Media and Public Relations, Mr. Habibu Nuhu Kila, confirmed the development to journalists in Dutse yesterday morning. Kila said: “It is true that Governor Badaru has traveled to Abuja to secure his nomination form for the 2023 presidential election.” He explained that his principal has the necessary wherewithal to lead the country to the Promised Land. The governor’s media aide stated that Badaru has the strength of character to change the tide if given the chance to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari, as he assured of his readiness to continue “with his positive programmes and policies.” THISDAY gathered that last Tuesday evening, the governor informed the party stakeholders of his ambition to contest the presidency. Badaru informed the gathering that he would seek the blessing of President Buhari before purchasing the form. The governor has since left the state capital, Dutse, for Abuja to obtain the form ahead of the presidential primary elections of the party.